# Supported Currencies

All monetary values in the API are expressed as **integers with 6 decimal places** of precision. The `currency` field in API responses uses the ISO 4217 abbreviation (or a platform-specific code for virtual currencies).

<Callout type="info">

The `balance.currency` field returned by the <a href="/docs/api/authenticate">Authenticate</a> endpoint will be one of the abbreviations listed below.

</Callout>

## Understanding Money

Monetary values in the Stake Engine are integers with **six decimal places** of precision. Currency impacts **only** the display layer - it does not affect gameplay logic.

| Raw Value | Actual Amount |
|-----------|--------------|
| `100000` | 0.10 |
| `1000000` | 1.00 |
| `10000000` | 10.00 |
| `100000000` | 100.00 |
| `1000000000` | 1,000.00 |

For example, to place a $1 bet, pass `1000000` as the `amount`.

## Fiat Currencies

| Currency | Abbreviation | Symbol | Decimals | Example |
|----------|--------------|--------|----------|---------|
| United States Dollar | `USD` | $ | 2 | $10.00 |
| Canadian Dollar | `CAD` | CA$ | 2 | CA$10.00 |
| Japanese Yen | `JPY` | ¥ | 0 | ¥10 |
| Euro | `EUR` | € | 2 | €10.00 |
